Name: acalculous cholecystitis
Definition: A lung disease that is defined as a recurrent or chronic collapse of the right middle lobe

Name: obsolete leukemic reticuloendotheliosis of intra-abdominal lymph nodes
Definition: A lung disease that is defined as a recurrent or chronic collapse of the right middle lobe
Synonym: Leukemic reticuloendotheliosis of intra-abdominal lymph nodes [dup] (disorder)

Name: emphysematous cholecystitis
Definition: Emphysematous cholecystitis is a bacterial infectious disease consisting of an inflammation of the gallbladder characterized by air-filled expansions in interstitial or subcutaneous tissues.

Name: xanthogranulomatous cholecystitis
Definition: Emphysematous cholecystitis is a bacterial infectious disease consisting of an inflammation of the gallbladder characterized by air-filled expansions in interstitial or subcutaneous tissues.
